cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.SDQ 

The paper proposes a novel method for speaker identification using Mel-frequency Cepstral coefficients (MFCCs) and dynamic information among adjacent frames. This method involves probability density function (PDF) estimation using the histogram transform (HT) method. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.SD (Sound)
- cs.CL (Computation and Language)
- cs.LG (Machine Learning)
- cs.SI (Speech and Audio Processing)
- cs.SDQ (Sound and Music Computing)
